{
  "texts": [
    "The Anna's Archive corpus claims to be the world's largest open-source and open-data library.",
    "It has currently gathered resources from Libgen, Sci-Hub, Z-Library, and Internet Archive Controlled Digital Lending.",
    "• BookCorpusOpen (Bandy and Vincent, 2021).",
    "The BookCorpusOpen corpus is a variant of Toronto Book Corpus.",
    "It comprises 17,868 book entries, with each entry containing a title and text."
  ]
}